# Decimal Reasoning

Common misconceptions:

children may believe:

```text id="p6o1qe"
decimal point
can be
ignored
```

or:

```text id="u3o9qe"
more decimal digits
=
larger answer
```

Some may:

```text id="c8o4qe"
add decimals
without
aligning places
```

Example:

students may solve:

```text id="k5o7qe"
2.3
+
0.45
```

and write:

```text id="n1o6qe"
2.75
or
2.48
```

without understanding:

```text id="t9o2qe"
tenths
and
hundredths
must align
```

Correct reasoning:

```text id="q4o8qe"
2.30
+
0.45
=
2.75
```

Students may also think:

```text id="v7o3qe"
0.4 × 10
=
0.40
```

instead of recognizing:

```text id="a2o5qe"
0.4 × 10
=
4
```

because:

```text id="g8o1rx"
digit values
change
by place
```

This skill teaches:

```text id="v3o6rt"
decimal-place reasoning
```

For Grade 5:

focus includes:

Decimal Operations:

* addition
* subtraction
* multiplication by powers of 10
* estimation
* reasonableness checks

Important idea:

```text id="j6o4qe"
decimal places
represent
different-sized units
```

